LUSAKA (Reuters) – Zambia’s health ministry on Wednesday confirmed its first two cases of COVID-19. “The patients are a Zambian couple that travelled to France on a 10-day holiday,” Health Minister Chitalu Chilufya said. (Reporting by Chris Mfula; Editing by Alex Richardson) This article was first published on Reuters Africa https://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFKBN2151M0-OZATP and is republished with its permission.